title: INsmh
description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from INsmh, skipping any feeds with errors.

items.title: Man Busted for Running Fake Embassy of Imaginary Nations
items.description: Harshvardhan Jain posed as ambassador for nonexistent places like Seborga and Westarctica, scamming people with job promises from a swanky bungalow. Police seized fake passports, cash, and luxury watches, suspecting money laundering. It's the diplomatic equivalent of a kid's treehouse club, but with real-world consequences and zero actual diplomacy.

items.title: Hot dog spill shuts down highway in Pennsylvania commuters’ wurst nightmare
items.description: In a moment that truly encapsulates modern American infrastructure, a truck hauling hot dogs turned Interstate 83 into a literal meat market after scraping a concrete divider and exploding its cargo all over the road. The Friday morning crash near Shrewsbury, PA, shut down traffic, bruised four unlucky commuters (non-fatally), and forced emergency crews into the dubious honor of shoveling warm, road-slicked franks into a dump truck. Even the fire chief had to admit the scene was a joke, though one that came with greasy boots and unexpected hot dog physics. SMH.
